pageContext.claim: “And you know in San Diego, as you know, it's going up and now it's up and here's what they did in California, they wanted the wall so badly, and so I did it, and I said you know, maybe I shouldn't do it politically. Let them ask, I did it, and now it's beautiful people not coming in, it's beautiful, right? In San Diego, and now they go out and say we didn't want the wall in the first place. They didn't. They wanted the wall desperately because they were being flooded with illegal immigrants.”
pageContext.analysis: San Diego does not support construction of the wall and it is not being constructed there. The Republican mayor of San Diego has said, "We already have a safe and secure border in San Diego built by the federal government." The city council passed a resolution opposing the border wall.
